COMPONENT NAME: RKM E-Business Suite COMPONENT VERSION: 10.1.3.3 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: 10.1.3.5.0 and above
DESCRIPTION - Reverse Knowledge Module - Reverse engineering Knowledge Module to retrieve Tables, Views, Flexfields and Interface-tables structures in E-Business Suite (columns, primary keys and foreign keys).
RESTRICTIONS - The tab Selective reverse cannot be used with this knowledge module. - Option "Min Rows" requires Oracle statistics to be computed on all tables. - If the Oracle user defined in the ODI data server is not the owner of the tables to reverse, you must define synonyms for this user on all tables you wish to reverse. Use user APPS for your connection.

List of the applications' short names as described in the APPLSYS.FND_APPLICATION table. These names must be between quotes and separated by commas. Eg: 'PO','GL' In case listed applications do not exist, no tables will be reversed.
If this option is selected, only installed and shared applications are reversed. Otherwise, all applications are reversed.
Minimum rows to reverse a table
Only tables with this minimum number of rows will be reversed. * A value of 0 means all the tables * Statistics have to be computed to use this option
Only objects whose descriptions match the mask pattern will be reversed.
If this option is selected, applications' flexfields are reversed
If this option is selected, applications' interface tables are reversed
insert into SNP_REV_KEY_COL ( I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, KEY_NAME, COL_NAME, POS ) Values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :KEY_NAME, :COL_NAME, :POS )

select /*+ RULE */ oat.table_name TABLE_NAME, pk.primary_key_name KEY_NAME, pkoac.column_name COL_NAME, pkc.primary_key_sequence POS from applsys.fnd_oracle_userid oau, applsys.fnd_product_installations oap, applsys.fnd_application oaa, applsys.fnd_tables oat, applsys.fnd_primary_keys pk, applsys.fnd_primary_key_columns pkc, applsys.fnd_columns pkoac where oaa.application_id = oap.application_id and oap.oracle_id = oau.oracle_id and oap.status <> decode('<%=odiRef.getOption("Only Installed Applications")%>','1','N','z') and oat.application_id = oaa.application_id and oaa.application_short_name in (<%=odiRef.getOption("Applications List")%>) and ''||oat.table_name like '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>%' and oat.application_id = pk.application_id and oat.table_id = pk.table_id and pk.application_id = pkc.application_id and pk.table_id = pkc.table_id and pk.primary_key_id = pkc.primary_key_id and pkoac.application_id = pkc.application_id and pkoac.table_id = pkc.table_id and pkoac.column_id = pkc.column_id and ''||oat.description like '<%=odiRef.getOption("Description Mask")%>%'

select idff.id_flex_name TABLE_NAME, oat.view_name RES_NAME, replace(oat.view_name, case when length(substr(oat.view_name, 1, instr(oat.view_name,'_'))) < 5 then substr(oat.view_name, 1, instr(oat.view_name,'_')) else '' end,'') TABLE_ALIAS, substr(oat.description, 1, 250) TABLE_DESC, substr('FLEX_' || oaa.application_short_name,1,35) SMOD_CODE from applsys.fnd_oracle_userid oau, applsys.fnd_product_installations oap, applsys.fnd_application oaa, applsys.fnd_views oat, applsys.fnd_id_flexs idff where oaa.application_id = oap.application_id and oap.oracle_id = oau.oracle_id and oat.application_id = oaa.application_id and idff.application_id = oaa.application_id and idff.concatenated_segs_view_name = oat.view_name and oaa.application_short_name in (<%=odiRef.getOption("Applications List")%>) and ''||oat.view_name like '<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_PATT")%>%' and oap.status <> decode('<%=odiRef.getOption("Only Installed Applications")%>','1','N','z') and ''||oat.description like '<%=odiRef.getOption("Description Mask")%>%'

insert into SNP_REV_TABLE ( I_MOD, TABLE_NAME, RES_NAME, TABLE_ALIAS, TABLE_TYPE, TABLE_DESC, IND_SHOW, R_COUNT, SMOD_CODE ) values ( <%=snpRef.getModel("ID")%>, :TABLE_NAME, :RES_NAME, :TABLE_ALIAS, 'T', :TABLE_DESC, '1', :R_COUNT, :SMOD_CODE )

Applications")%>','1','N','z') and oat.application_id = oaa.application_id and oaa.application_short_name in (<%=odiRef.getOption("Applications List")%>) and t.owner = oau.oracle_username and '%INTERFACE%' and ''||oat.description like '<%=odiRef.getOption("Description Mask")%>%' and instr(';'||'<%=odiRef.getModel("REV_OBJ_TYPE")%>'||';', ';T;') > 0 ) t where t.owner = c.owner and
